{"ts":"2026-07-04T19:20:15.349Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"## Context\nSplit out of pm-8t5x (claim test-and-set): once claim correctly CONFLICTs on held items, N parallel agents that each run `pm next` will all be recommended the SAME top item, all try to claim it, and N-1 will bounce. The missing primitive is an atomic \"give me my own item\".\n\n## Design sketch\n`pm claim --next` (or `pm next --claim`): compute the pm next recommendation and claim it in one operation; on already_claimed_by conflict, retry with the next-ranked candidate (bounded, e.g. 10 candidates) until one claim succeeds; return the claimed item with the same rationale payload pm next emits. Honors --if-available semantics naturally (skip held candidates instead of erroring). Requires pm-8t5x semantics (deps: blocked_by) and benefits from pm-2muu's lock wait.\n\n## Definition of done\nN-parallel `pm claim --next` stress: N distinct items claimed, zero double-grants; recommendation rationale preserved in output; MCP action + contracts + completion + docs wired per the new-command checklist (grep replicate every site); spec covers conflict-retry and exhausted-candidates paths."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-114v"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"pm claim --next: atomically claim the next actionable item so parallel agents each get distinct work"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Companion to pm-8t5x. pm next + pm claim as separate steps race under parallel agents: all N agents get the same recommendation and N-1 fail their claim. Add an atomic recommend+claim with bounded retry over next-ranked candidates so each parallel agent receives a distinct item. Idea originated in the 2026-07-03 concurrency audit (recorded inside pm-8t5x's fix sketch); promoted to its own tracked Feature by the 2026-07-04 metadata audit."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","cli","concurrency"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-04T19:20:15.349Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-04T19:20:15.349Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":240},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"pm claim --next claims a distinct item per parallel agent (stress-verified, zero double-grants); bounded candidate retry on already_claimed_by; output includes pm next rationale; wired across MCP/contracts/completion/docs per new-command checklist"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-dj98"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"medium"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"024ad07d1f91cd39acc83d6007b0aff72fa3c1556c304e7d5f2c84437172fe71","message":""}
